### estimateBitMaskedAndLowerBound() {#a437967d8acddbcdb8cb345412f22f9dd}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static APInt estimateBitMaskedAndLowerBound (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantrange">ConstantRange</a> &amp; LHS, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantrange">ConstantRange</a> &amp; RHS)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Estimate the &#39;bit-masked AND&#39; operation&#39;s lower bound.

E.g., given two ranges as follows (single quotes are separators and have no meaning here),

LHS = &#91;10&#39;00101&#39;1, ; LLo 10&#39;10000&#39;0&#93; ; LHi RHS = &#91;10&#39;11111&#39;0, ; RLo 10&#39;11111&#39;1&#93; ; RHi

we know that the higher 2 bits of the result is always 10; and we also notice that RHS&#91;1:6&#93; are always 1, so the result&#91;1:6&#93; cannot be less than LHS&#91;1:6&#93; (i.e., 00101). Thus, the lower bound is 10&#39;00101&#39;0.

The algorithm is as follows,
<ul>
<li>we first calculate a mask to find the higher common bits by Mask = ~((LLo ^ LHi) | (RLo ^ RHi) | (LLo ^ RLo)); Mask = clear all non-leading-ones bits in Mask; in the example, the Mask is set to 11&#39;00000&#39;0;</li>
<li>calculate a new mask by setting all common leading bits to 1 in RHS, and keeping the longest leading ones (i.e., 11&#39;11111&#39;0 in the example);</li>
<li>return (LLo &amp; new mask) as the lower bound;</li>
<li>repeat the step 2 and 3 with LHS and RHS swapped, and update the lower bound with the larger one.</li>
</ul>

Definition at line <a href="#l01547">1547</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/constantrange-cpp">ConstantRange.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00872" /><CodeLine lineNumber="872"><Highlight kind="normal">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantrange/#a8cbe37c4ba99ff3bc99338fcc618c618">ConstantRange</a> Union(DstTySize, </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">/&#42;isFullSet=&#42;/</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">false</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00873" /><CodeLine lineNumber="873"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00874" /><CodeLine lineNumber="874"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Analyze wrapped sets in their two parts: &#91;0, Upper) \\/ &#91;Lower, MaxValue&#93;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00875" /><CodeLine lineNumber="875"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We use the non-wrapped set code to analyze the &#91;Lower, MaxValue) part, and</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00876" /><CodeLine lineNumber="876"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// then we do the union with &#91;MaxValue, Upper)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00877" /><CodeLine lineNumber="877"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantrange/#aa1a0c35225268e93dc3afd67e079f826">isUpperWrapped</a>()) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00878" /><CodeLine lineNumber="878"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If Upper is greater than or equal to MaxValue(DstTy), it covers the whole</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00879" /><CodeLine lineNumber="879"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// truncated range.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00880" /><CodeLine lineNumber="880"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Upper.getActiveBits() &gt; DstTySize || Upper.countr&#95;one() == DstTySize)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00881" /><CodeLine lineNumber="881"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> getFull(DstTySize);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00882" /><CodeLine lineNumber="882"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00883" /><CodeLine lineNumber="883"><Highlight kind="normal">    Union = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantrange/#a8cbe37c4ba99ff3bc99338fcc618c618">ConstantRange</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint/#a331d69b5f93e47e7c596062b77dd5913">APInt::getMaxValue</a>(DstTySize),Upper.trunc(DstTySize));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00884" /><CodeLine lineNumber="884"><Highlight kind="normal">    UpperDiv.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint/#ab6fff8a97bcb55e50e9be0ecf0c99b63">setAllBits</a>();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00885" /><CodeLine lineNumber="885"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00886" /><CodeLine lineNumber="886"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Union covers the MaxValue case, so return if the remaining range is just</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00887" /><CodeLine lineNumber="887"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// MaxValue(DstTy).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00888" /><CodeLine lineNumber="888"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (LowerDiv == UpperDiv)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00889" /><CodeLine lineNumber="889"><Highlight kind="normal">      </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Union;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00890" /><CodeLine lineNumber="890"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00891" /><CodeLine lineNumber="891"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00892" /><CodeLine lineNumber="892"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Chop off the most significant bits that are past the destination bitwidth.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00893" /><CodeLine lineNumber="893"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (LowerDiv.getActiveBits() &gt; DstTySize) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00894" /><CodeLine lineNumber="894"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Mask to just the signficant bits and subtract from LowerDiv/UpperDiv.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00895" /><CodeLine lineNumber="895"><Highlight kind="normal">    <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint">APInt</a> Adjust = LowerDiv &amp; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint/#aeaf22e8d92fd978a5eca9ab031994399">APInt::getBitsSetFrom</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantrange/#ad7f81241f958a1f5917a3410942d3199">getBitWidth</a>(), DstTySize);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00896" /><CodeLine lineNumber="896"><Highlight kind="normal">    LowerDiv -= Adjust;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00897" /><CodeLine lineNumber="897"><Highlight kind="normal">    UpperDiv -= Adjust;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00898" /><CodeLine lineNumber="898"><Highlight kind="normal">  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00899" /><CodeLine lineNumber="899"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="900"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> UpperDivWidth = UpperDiv.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint/#a3015474e70e59c0a3ed4f9f0e8644b75">getActiveBits</a>();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00901" /><CodeLine lineNumber="901"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (UpperDivWidth &lt;= DstTySize)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="902"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantrange/#a8cbe37c4ba99ff3bc99338fcc618c618">ConstantRange</a>(LowerDiv.trunc(DstTySize),</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><Highlight kind="normal">                         UpperDiv.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint/#a317c64fd4cfebc88e79387b3821a629d">trunc</a>(DstTySize)).unionWith(Union);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00904" /><CodeLine lineNumber="904"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00905" /><CodeLine lineNumber="905"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The truncated value wraps around. Check if we can do better than fullset.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00906" /><CodeLine lineNumber="906"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (UpperDivWidth == DstTySize + 1) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01522" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1522"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01523" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1523"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Estimate the &#39;bit-masked AND&#39; operation&#39;s lower bound.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01524" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1524"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01525" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1525"><Highlight kind="comment">/// E.g., given two ranges as follows (single quotes are separators and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01526" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1526"><Highlight kind="comment">/// have no meaning here),</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01527" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1527"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01528" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1528"><Highlight kind="comment">///   LHS = &#91;10&#39;00101&#39;1,  ; LLo</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01529" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1529"><Highlight kind="comment">///          10&#39;10000&#39;0&#93;  ; LHi</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01530" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1530"><Highlight kind="comment">///   RHS = &#91;10&#39;11111&#39;0,  ; RLo</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01531" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1531"><Highlight kind="comment">///          10&#39;11111&#39;1&#93;  ; RHi</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01532" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1532"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01533" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1533"><Highlight kind="comment">/// we know that the higher 2 bits of the result is always 10; and we also</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01534" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1534"><Highlight kind="comment">/// notice that RHS&#91;1:6&#93; are always 1, so the result&#91;1:6&#93; cannot be less than</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01535" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1535"><Highlight kind="comment">/// LHS&#91;1:6&#93; (i.e., 00101). Thus, the lower bound is 10&#39;00101&#39;0.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01536" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1536"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01537" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1537"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The algorithm is as follows,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01538" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1538"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 1 we first calculate a mask to find the higher common bits by</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01539" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1539"><Highlight kind="comment">///       Mask = ~((LLo ^ LHi) | (RLo ^ RHi) | (LLo ^ RLo));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01540" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1540"><Highlight kind="comment">///       Mask = clear all non-leading-ones bits in Mask;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01541" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1541"><Highlight kind="comment">///    in the example, the Mask is set to 11&#39;00000&#39;0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01542" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1542"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 2 calculate a new mask by setting all common leading bits to 1 in RHS, and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01543" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1543"><Highlight kind="comment">///    keeping the longest leading ones (i.e., 11&#39;11111&#39;0 in the example);</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01544" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1544"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 3 return (LLo &amp; new mask) as the lower bound;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01545" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1545"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 4 repeat the step 2 and 3 with LHS and RHS swapped, and update the lower</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01546" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1546"><Highlight kind="comment">///    bound with the larger one.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01547" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1547" lineLink="#a437967d8acddbcdb8cb345412f22f9dd"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint">APInt</a> <a href="#a437967d8acddbcdb8cb345412f22f9dd">estimateBitMaskedAndLowerBound</a>(</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantrange">ConstantRange</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/x86partialreduction-cpp/#a9e1483f7215664a2315c53c3558d9a8d">LHS</a>,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01548" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1548"><Highlight kind="normal">                                            </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantrange">ConstantRange</a> &amp;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/x86partialreduction-cpp/#a87b8bfbbe9d8f7146d7f20a5fb42efd0">RHS</a>) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01549" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1549"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#abee0df5f7f703bb4462aba260ba0a60f">BitWidth</a> = <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/x86partialreduction-cpp/#a9e1483f7215664a2315c53c3558d9a8d">LHS</a>.getBitWidth();</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1550"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If either is full set or unsigned wrapped, then the range must contain &#39;0&#39;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01551" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1551"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// which leads the lower bound to 0</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01552" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1552"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> ((<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/x86partialreduction-cpp/#a9e1483f7215664a2315c53c3558d9a8d">LHS</a>.isFullSet() || <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/x86partialreduction-cpp/#a87b8bfbbe9d8f7146d7f20a5fb42efd0">RHS</a>.isFullSet()) ||</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01553" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1553"><Highlight kind="normal">      (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/x86partialreduction-cpp/#a9e1483f7215664a2315c53c3558d9a8d">LHS</a>.isWrappedSet() || <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/x86/x86partialreduction-cpp/#a87b8bfbbe9d8f7146d7f20a5fb42efd0">RHS</a>.isWrappedSet()))</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1554"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/apint/#add4e37b60ea64faafbc9a5bf3e27280f">APInt::getZero</a>(<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#abee0df5f7f703bb4462aba260ba0a60f">BitWidth</a>);</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01560" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1560"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01561" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1561"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Calculate the mask for the higher common bits.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01562" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1562"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">auto</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Mask = ~((LLo ^ LHi) | (RLo ^ RHi) | (LLo ^ RLo));</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01563" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1563"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> LeadingOnes = Mask.countLeadingOnes();</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1600"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &lt;=&gt;  ~(~a &amp; ~b) &lt;= ~x</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02105" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2105"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Otherwise, the minimum is the popcount of LCP + 1</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02108" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2108"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If Max is &#123;LCP, 111...&#125;, the maximum is the popcount of LCP + (BitWidth -</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02112" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2112"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> MaxBits = LCPPopCount + (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#abee0df5f7f703bb4462aba260ba0a60f">BitWidth</a> - LCPLength) -</Highlight></CodeLine>
